.TH HSH 1 "January 2024" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX command line interpreter. It reads commands from standard input and executes them. The shell can handle both interactive and non-interactive modes, supports command execution with arguments, and properly manages paths and whitespace.

.SH FEATURES
.IP \[bu]
Executes commands with arguments
.IP \[bu]
Handles the PATH environment variable
.IP \[bu]
Implements built-in command: exit
.IP \[bu]
Supports both interactive and non-interactive mode
.IP \[bu]
Handles absolute and relative paths
.IP \[bu]
Manages leading and trailing whitespace
.IP \[bu]
Works with or without environment variables
.IP \[bu]
Proper error handling for non-existent commands

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell

.SH COMMAND EXECUTION
The shell supports various command formats:
.TP
.B Basic commands:
ls, pwd, etc.
.TP
.B Commands with arguments:
ls -l, ls /var
.TP
.B Absolute paths:
/bin/ls, /usr/bin/pwd
.TP
.B Relative paths:
./program, ../directory/program
.TP
.B Commands with whitespace:
    ls    ,    ls -l    

.SH ENVIRONMENT
The shell can operate with or without environment variables. When environment variables are removed (using env -i), the shell continues to function properly for commands with absolute paths.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Basic command:
.B $ ls
.TP
Command with arguments:
.B $ ls -l
.TP
Absolute path:
.B $ /bin/ls
.TP
Command with whitespace:
.B $     ls     
.TP
Multiple commands:
.B $ ls
.B $ pwd
.TP
Without environment:
.B $ env -i ./hsh

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 127
Command not found

.SH AUTHOR
Frederic Bourouliou <frederic.bourouliou@gmail.com>

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh(1) 